description: Tests criteria for a custom data identifier.

parameters.name: ignoreWords
parameters.description: An array that lists specific character sequences (ignore words) to exclude from the results. If the text matched by the regular expression contains any string in this array, Amazon Macie ignores it. The array can contain as many as 10 ignore words. Each ignore word can contain 4-90 UTF-8 characters. Ignore words are case sensitive. (string) ---

parameters.name: keywords
parameters.description: An array that lists specific character sequences (keywords), one of which must precede and be within proximity (maximumMatchDistance) of the regular expression to match. The array can contain as many as 50 keywords. Each keyword can contain 3-90 UTF-8 characters. Keywords aren't case sensitive. (string) ---

parameters.name: regex
parameters.description: The regular expression (regex) that defines the pattern to match. The expression can contain as many as 512 characters.

parameters.name: sampleText
parameters.description: The sample text to inspect by using the custom data identifier. The text can contain as many as 1,000 characters.

nested_items.name: matchCount
nested_items.description: The number of occurrences of sample text that matched the criteria specified by the custom data identifier.
